{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"coaching":[{"coaching":"Plan how AC6 pytest invocation argument ordering will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"block","finding_refs":["fe93358d820e9d458"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"AC6 pytest invocation argument ordering"},{"coaching":"Pin down documentation update verification examples with a concrete worked example.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f9b66ad60f414048e","f34f82fd2d27f190f"],"move_id":"6","move_name":"specification by example","subject":"documentation update verification examples"},{"coaching":"Test the riskiest assumption behind JIRA_BIND event type existence assumption first.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f9de583775f1c9f0d"],"move_id":"4","move_name":"riskiest-assumption test","subject":"JIRA_BIND event type existence assumption"},{"coaching":"Test the riskiest assumption behind gen_types const-to-Literal extension feasibility first.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f62c4501510df6c1c"],"move_id":"4","move_name":"riskiest-assumption test","subject":"gen_types const-to-Literal extension feasibility"},{"coaching":"Pin down process_edit immutable-field guard insertion point with a concrete worked example.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f35a1802a4199ff0e"],"move_id":"6","move_name":"specification by example","subject":"process_edit immutable-field guard insertion point"},{"coaching":"Pin down process_snapshot legacy-channel handling boundary with a concrete worked example.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f10693fb223d27c27"],"move_id":"6","move_name":"specification by example","subject":"process_snapshot legacy-channel handling boundary"}],"coverage":{"counts":{"advisory_overflow":0,"advisory_surfaced":5,"blocking":1,"dropped":14,"indeterminate":0},"det":{"P1":{"ac_items":7,"blocking":false,"clarity_score":7,"name":"readiness-shape","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P2":{"blocking":false,"name":"resolution","ran":true,"references":0,"resolved":0,"status":"pass"},"P3":{"blocking":false,"name":"package-existence","packages":0,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P4":{"ac_items":7,"blocking":false,"desc_chars":7557,"file_impact":15,"name":"oversize","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P5":{"blocking":false,"children":0,"name":"task-dag","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P6":{"ac_items":7,"blocking":false,"name":"ac-quality","ran":true,"status":"fail","verify_commands_linted":4,"verify_lint_abstained":4},"P7":{"blocking":false,"destructive_hits":[],"name":"destructive-sniff","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P8":{"blocking":false,"budget_tokens":868000,"name":"reviewability","plan_tokens":1903,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P9":{"applicable":true,"blocking":false,"file_impact":15,"name":"file-impact-coverage","ran":true,"status":"pass"}},"floored_criteria":["G6","T11"],"floored_finding_ids":["f35a1802a4199ff0e","f10693fb223d27c27"],"llm_ran":true,"metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":221.7,"llm_calls":30,"llm_ms":679510.3,"total_ms":679844.1,"verify_requests":31},"narrowed":true,"remediation":{"baseline":"signature","eligible":true,"reasons":{"code_unchanged":true,"plan_changed":true,"prior_sidecar":true,"registry_unchanged":true,"signed":true,"within_window":true}},"routing":{"agent_tier":["A1","E4","G1G2","G6","G7","T1","T10","T11","T13","T14","T3","T5c","T8","removal-rationale"],"single_turn":["COH","E1","E2","E3","E5","E6","F1","F4","G5","T2","T4","T5b","T5d","T5e","T6","T7","T9","hedge"]}},"findings":[{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Split AC6's proving command so the `-k projections` filter applies only to `test_creation_channel.py` and the contract files run without a `-k` filter (e.g. two separate `uv run pytest` invocations, or `uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/facades/test_creation_channel.py -k projections && uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_ticket_state.py tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_outputs.py tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_coverage.py && python -m rebar.schemas.gen_types --check`).","cohort":["E2","E6","F1"],"criteria":["E6","F1"],"decision":"block","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["\"uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/facades/test_creation_channel.py -k projections tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_ticket_state.py tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_outputs.py tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_coverage.py\"","pytest `-k` expression is applied globally to all collected nodes across all supplied paths; contract test functions not named '*projections*' are deselected silently","VERIFY-COMMAND DEFECT type 3 (wrong argv behaviour) and type 5 (missing cardinality assertion — zero collected tests from contract files is not an error)"],"finding":"AC6's proving command applies the `-k projections` filter globally to all pytest paths in the same invocation, meaning tests in `test_schema_ticket_state.py`, `test_schema_outputs.py`, and `test_schema_coverage.py` whose names do not contain 'projections' will be silently deselected. Pytest exits 0 with 'no tests ran' (or runs only a subset) from those contract files, so the command can pass green without actually exercising the contract-file coverage it claims to prove.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fe93358d820e9d458","impact":1.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria, AC6 proving command","norm_id":"n6338e2f60d2b9904","priority":1.0,"reason":"high-priority+criterion-opted-in","scenarios":["An agent runs the AC6 command, the contract files contribute zero tests (none are named 'projections'), pytest exits 0, the criterion is marked done, but the schema contract is never actually verified."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"Replace the single AC6 command with:\n```\nuv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/facades/test_creation_channel.py -k projections && \\\nuv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_ticket_state.py tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_outputs.py tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_coverage.py && \\\npython -m rebar.schemas.gen_types --check\n```","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"broken_oracle","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"high","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an AC (or extend AC6) with a concrete in-session check that the six-value enum and `creation_channel`/`creation_channel_inferred` fields appear in both `docs/event-schema.md` and `docs/output-schemas.md` (e.g. `grep -q 'creation_channel' docs/event-schema.md && grep -q 'creation_channel' docs/output-schemas.md`).","cohort":["E2","E6","F1"],"criteria":["E6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Files: 'docs/event-schema.md and docs/output-schemas.md: local channel contract.'","No AC references a grep, diff, or prose check confirming the six-value enum or creation_channel field appears in either doc file.","ABSENCE: no proving command for the documentation deliverable."],"finding":"The plan lists `docs/event-schema.md` and `docs/output-schemas.md` in the Files section as deliverables, but no AC requires verifying that those docs were updated. An agent could skip the documentation updates and all ACs would still pass.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f9b66ad60f414048e","impact":1.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Files section and Acceptance Criteria (all ACs)","norm_id":"n013e5b1570094135","priority":1.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Documentation is omitted or only partially updated; all pytest ACs pass; the story is closed as complete with out-of-date docs."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"missing_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"low","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a verifiable docs-check step to AC6's proof command (e.g., a grep/script that asserts the six enum values appear in docs/event-schema.md and docs/output-schemas.md, or a docs contract test under tests/interfaces/contracts/).","cohort":["COH","E1","T5d"],"criteria":["E1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["AC6 text: 'ticket_state JSON Schema, generated TicketState types, runtime show/list/search/export outputs, plus docs expose the same six-value enum'","AC6 proof: 'uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/facades/test_creation_channel.py -k projections tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_ticket_state.py tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_outputs.py tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_coverage.py && python -m rebar.schemas.gen_types --check'","Files section lists docs/event-schema.md and docs/output-schemas.md as deliverables with no corresponding test/lint command"],"finding":"AC6 claims 'docs expose the same six-value enum' as part of its done definition, but the proof command (`uv run pytest ... && python -m rebar.schemas.gen_types --check`) contains no step that verifies docs/event-schema.md or docs/output-schemas.md content. An implementer could skip the documentation update entirely and still pass all listed AC6 checks.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f34f82fd2d27f190f","impact":1.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — AC6 proof command; Files — docs/event-schema.md and docs/output-schemas.md","norm_id":"n10761269811c78f2","priority":1.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Implementer passes all pytest checks but leaves docs stale; reviewer has no automated gate to catch the omission."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"Add a small contract test or shell assertion — e.g., `python -c \"import pathlib; doc=pathlib.Path('docs/event-schema.md').read_text(); [assert v in doc for v in ('cli','mcp','python','jira','import','unknown')]\"` — appended to the AC6 proof command, or extract it into tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_coverage.py which is already in the proof list.","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"missing_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"low","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Remove or replace `JIRA_BIND` from all plan references (What section and AC5): either drop it (it doesn't exist) or name the actual Jira-related event type(s) that should be covered by the immutable-field guard.","cohort":["G1G2"],"criteria":["G1G2"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Search for 'JIRA_BIND' across all source files returns zero matches in src/rebar/.","src/rebar/reducer/_version.py KNOWN_EVENT_TYPES frozenset: CREATE, STATUS, COMMENT, LINK, UNLINK, BRIDGE_ALERT, REVERT, EDIT, FILE_IMPACT, VERIFY_COMMANDS, SIGNATURE, ARCHIVED, SNAPSHOT, WORKFLOW_RUN, WORKFLOW_STEP, COMMITS, TAG_DELTA, KEY_ADD, KEY_REVOKE — JIRA_BIND is not present.","Plan AC5 test: `uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/facades/test_creation_channel.py -k immutable` — the test would need to exercise a JIRA_BIND event that cannot be produced."],"finding":"`JIRA_BIND` is named in the plan as a real existing event type whose processor must ignore `creation_channel`, but it does not exist anywhere in the codebase — absent from `KNOWN_EVENT_TYPES`, `_processors.py`, and every event-dispatch table.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f9de583775f1c9f0d","impact":0.85,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section (immutable-field guard paragraph): 'STATUS, LINK, JIRA_BIND, plus other specialized events also cannot replace genesis provenance'; AC5: 'STATUS, LINK, JIRA_BIND, plus other specialized events also cannot replace genesis provenance'","norm_id":"ncb89f89e8202f586","priority":0.5312,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["The immutable-field guard test (-k immutable) would either fail to simulate a JIRA_BIND event (no such event type exists to write/replay) or silently pass without exercising the named code path.","A developer implementing the immutable-field guard following the plan's example would look for a JIRA_BIND processor to update, find none, and either skip it or introduce confusion."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"Replace `JIRA_BIND` with the actual event types emitted by the Jira reconciler (e.g. `BRIDGE_ALERT`, or clarify that no Jira-specific event type currently exists in KNOWN_EVENT_TYPES and the guard only needs to cover EDIT/STATUS/LINK/UNLINK/etc.).","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"medium","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.75,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Explicitly specify in the plan that a new `if 'const' in node:` branch must be added to `gen_types._pytype()` *before* the `jtype is None → Any` fallback, and that a contract test must assert the emitted annotation is exactly `Literal[True]` (not `Any`).","cohort":["E4"],"criteria":["E4"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["gen_types.py _pytype() checks: '$ref', 'enum', then dispatches on jtype (list, array, object, None). No 'const' branch exists.","A {\"const\": true} schema node has neither '$ref', 'enum', nor a 'type' key, so it falls through all existing branches to 'if jtype is None: return Any'.","Plan states: 'Extend src/rebar/schemas/gen_types.py so JSON Schema {\"const\": true} generates Literal[True], then regenerate src/rebar/types.py'","ABSENCE: grep for 'const' in gen_types.py returns no matches."],"finding":"The plan asserts 'Extend src/rebar/schemas/gen_types.py so JSON Schema {\"const\": true} generates Literal[True]', implying this is a straightforward extension. However, the current _pytype() method in gen_types.py has zero handling for 'const' — a node like {\"const\": true} falls through to 'jtype = node.get(\"type\")' which returns None, producing 'Any'. No branch in _pytype() checks for 'const'. This means the extension is non-trivial: a new branch must be inserted before the existing type-dispatch logic, and it must be placed carefully so it runs before the 'jtype is None → Any' fallback. The plan does not call out that this is a materially new code-path in the generator, which could cause an implementor to underestimate the change.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f62c4501510df6c1c","impact":0.67,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section: 'Extend src/rebar/schemas/gen_types.py so JSON Schema {\"const\": true} generates Literal[True]'; Files: src/rebar/schemas/gen_types.py _pytype() method lines 115-149","norm_id":"n55fe86a3497208de","priority":0.4188,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An implementor adds the creation_channel_inferred field to ticket_state.schema.json as {\"const\": true} but forgets to add the const branch to gen_types._pytype(), causing the regenerated types.py to emit 'Any' rather than 'Literal[True]' — the AC check 'gen_types renders const true as Literal[True]' fails silently unless the --check gate is run.","The AC verification command 'python -m rebar.schemas.gen_types --check' passes only if the committed types.py was generated with the updated generator — a stale types.py pre-committed before the generator is updated would cause a false pass in some CI orderings."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Add to the gen_types.py extension description: 'Insert a new branch in _pytype(): if \"const\" in node: self._used_typing.add(\"Literal\"); return f\"Literal[{node[\"const\"]!r}]\". This must precede the jtype-dispatch block. Add a unit assertion in the schema contract tests that gen_types._Generator()._pytype({\"const\": True}) == \"Literal[True]\"'.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":null,"blocking_enabled":null,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["P6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["5 criterion line(s) bundle multiple deliverables with 'and' (split so each is independently verifiable)."],"finding":"Acceptance-criteria / definition-of-done quality issues.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f607dd457c67f9209","impact":0.4,"is_primary":null,"location":"","norm_id":"ned06ebc801a522e3","priority":0.4,"reason":null,"scenarios":[],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Split compound criteria, replace subjective terms with observable outcomes, and state how each is verified.","tier":"DET","validity":1.0,"verification":null},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add one sentence to the What section explicitly stating that this story never writes `creation_channel_inferred=true`; only e622 does so, and the schema/types are added here solely to establish the contract e622 will use.","cohort":["E2","E6","F1"],"criteria":["E2"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'A legacy CREATE with no value provisionally projects creation_channel=unknown without creation_channel_inferred.'","'Child e622 treats absent/None/unknown-without-marker as unresolved legacy input so positive Jira inference can replace this provisional fallback.'","No explicit statement that this story's code paths NEVER set creation_channel_inferred=true; an agent must infer this from context."],"finding":"The plan introduces `creation_channel_inferred` as a schema field and describes its semantics (omitted for explicit channels, omitted for unknown-legacy, set to `true` only by e622 inference), but never explicitly states that this story never emits `creation_channel_inferred=true`. An implementing agent might attempt to emit the marker in some projection path, or conversely wonder whether the `{\"const\": true}` schema field must be tested here. The condition under which it is first populated is left implicit.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fbe329ff9724775ec","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section, paragraph 5 ('Store creation_channel in CREATE.data...'); AC4 and AC6","norm_id":"n5c9db870656343ef","priority":0.099,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["An agent adds code to set creation_channel_inferred=true for some cases, or writes a test asserting it, creating a contract conflict with e622; alternatively, the agent omits the field entirely from the schema and tests, treating it as out-of-scope."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an explicit rollback path or expand-contract sequence for the create_core signature change: e.g., temporarily give creation_channel a sentinel default (creation_channel=_UNSET) that raises a descriptive error, ship callers in a preparatory commit, then remove the sentinel — or document the atomic-commit constraint and a named revert procedure.","cohort":["T2","T4","T7"],"criteria":["T4"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'Make composer.create_core require an internal keyword-only creation_channel with no default, so omission raises TypeError at the internal seam'","'Every existing caller is updated in this story.'","No rollback path, feature flag, or expand-contract sequence is described anywhere in the plan."],"finding":"The plan makes create_core's creation_channel a required keyword-only parameter with no default, making every existing call site a TypeError at import/call time until updated. The plan says 'every existing caller is updated in this story,' which acknowledges the break, but provides no rollback path or expand-contract sequencing. If the story is partially merged, deployed with missed callers, or reverted mid-flight, there is no described mechanism to restore prior behavior without a full revert of all touched files simultaneously.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fb0feb255bd03e930","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section: 'Make composer.create_core require an internal keyword-only creation_channel with no default'; Files: src/rebar/_commands/composer.py, src/rebar/_lib_writes.py, src/rebar/_mcp_writes.py, src/rebar/_commands/idea.py, src/rebar/_commands/session_log.py, src/rebar/_commands/identity.py","norm_id":"n4ac08f37ce573aad","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["A partial merge leaves one caller unpatched; the function becomes uncallable until the caller is also updated.","A hot-fix revert of composer.py without reverting all callers leaves TypeError-raising callers in production.","A missed caller in a test-only path silently breaks the test suite rather than failing at build time."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Introduce a sentinel default `_UNSET = object()` on `creation_channel` in a first commit; update all callers in subsequent commits; remove the sentinel in a final commit. This makes each intermediate state valid and individually revertable.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.25,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"moderate","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Audit all existing schema files for pre-existing const: true (or other const) usages and explicitly state in the plan which generated-type changes are intentional side-effects of the gen_types extension, so the diff in types.py is fully accounted for.","cohort":["T2","T4","T7"],"criteria":["T4"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'Extend src/rebar/schemas/gen_types.py so JSON Schema {\"const\": true} generates Literal[True], then regenerate src/rebar/types.py through the existing schema generator.'","No statement in the plan about whether existing schemas contain const: true fields or what the current generated output for them is."],"finding":"The gen_types.py extension renders JSON Schema {\"const\": true} as Literal[True]. The plan does not acknowledge whether any existing schema field already uses const: true (or any other const value) and would therefore have its generated type silently changed by this rule. If pre-existing const usages exist, the regenerated types.py will differ from the current committed version in ways that are not described as intentional, potentially breaking downstream type-checked consumers.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fcdf3d29165275d05","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section: 'Extend src/rebar/schemas/gen_types.py so JSON Schema {\"const\": true} generates Literal[True]'; Files: src/rebar/schemas/gen_types.py, src/rebar/types.py","norm_id":"ncaa41090e477348c","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["A pre-existing schema field uses const: true and currently generates a different type expression; regeneration silently changes that type, breaking type-checked callers.","The --check flag on gen_types catches the diff but the plan doesn't call this out as an expected/intentional diff, causing confusion."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an ADR or CLAUDE.md section capturing (a) the explicit-boundary-threading decision over stack inspection / context-local state, (b) the _IMMUTABLE_EDIT_FIELDS frozenset pattern and its invariant, and (c) the const→Literal[True] codegen convention, so maintainers can evolve any of these three without guessing intent.","cohort":["T5b","T5e","T9"],"criteria":["T5e"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'docs/event-schema.md and docs/output-schemas.md: local channel contract' — only schema-level docs are listed","Approach Rationale explains the threading choice but has no corresponding durable design doc","ABSENCE: no ADR, CLAUDE.md, or design-doc file appears in the Files list"],"finding":"Three novel architectural decisions are introduced — explicit boundary threading for creation_channel, the _IMMUTABLE_EDIT_FIELDS guard as a new reducer pattern, and the const→Literal[True] codegen extension — but the plan's documentation scope covers only event-schema.md and output-schemas.md (schema-level docs), with no ADR or CLAUDE.md update to capture the design rationale for future maintainers.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f65d80ee662845a15","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Files section / docs/event-schema.md and docs/output-schemas.md; Approach Rationale section","norm_id":"n295c1fca7a9df8ad","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["A future contributor adds a new channel value and doesn't realize the frozenset, schema, runtime constant, and contract test must all move together because the decision isn't captured outside the code.","The _IMMUTABLE_EDIT_FIELDS pattern is replicated inconsistently in a follow-on reducer because its rationale wasn't documented."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Create docs/decisions/creation-channel-boundary.md (or an ADR-NNN entry) with three sections: (1) why explicit keyword threading was chosen; (2) the _IMMUTABLE_EDIT_FIELDS contract (what belongs there and the invariant that genesis provenance is write-once); (3) the gen_types const→Literal[True] rule and how to extend it. Reference this doc from CLAUDE.md under 'Architectural decisions'.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.1429,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"na","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a structured log line (e.g., `logger.error('creation_channel rejected: %r caller=%s', value, caller_hint)`) inside validate_creation_channel so rejection events are visible in server logs without a debugger.","cohort":["T5b","T5e","T9"],"criteria":["T5b"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'create_core calls this helper, so every local live writer rejects unknown or off-vocabulary values' — no mention of logging the rejection","ABSENCE: no log/metric/trace instrumentation for the validation failure path appears anywhere in the plan"],"finding":"The validate_creation_channel rejection path — the only new error state introduced by this plan — has no instrumentation (log line, metric, or structured error context) mentioned, so operators cannot distinguish a misconfigured caller from a bug without a debugger.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fa0d53aecc6b7db39","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section: 'create_core calls this helper, so every local live writer rejects unknown or off-vocabulary values'; AC line: 'New local writers reject unknown or values outside the closed enum'","norm_id":"n9522165c5027af9c","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["A newly added MCP tool passes a typo'd channel string; create_core raises a TypeError/ValueError but the error disappears into the MCP error response with no server-side log entry, making it hard to diagnose in production.","An internal automation script accidentally omits the channel keyword; the TypeError is caught by a broad except block upstream, silently degrading to a no-op creation."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"In reducer/_version.py, before raising the ValueError/TypeError, emit `import logging; logging.getLogger(__name__).error('Invalid creation_channel %r rejected at create_core boundary', value)`. This single line satisfies observability for the new failure point.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"na","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an AC (or extend AC2/AC1) that explicitly verifies the creation_channel recorded on the identity CREATE event emitted by ensure_identity_for when triggered as a side-effect of an MCP or CLI create_ticket call, OR document that this side-effect path intentionally records python and will be corrected in e622.","cohort":["E5","G5"],"criteria":["E5"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan: 'Add creation_channel=\\'python\\' keyword parameters to create_identity_core and ensure_identity_for. Local library callers use that default; identity_cli passes cli.'","Plan does NOT state that composer.create_core or _lib_writes.py propagates the caller's channel into the ensure_identity_for call triggered as a side-effect of ticket creation.","AC2 states 'create_identity' directly but does not address the identity CREATE event emitted via ensure_identity_for during create_ticket with channel=mcp.","ABSENCE: no AC line tests that ensure_identity_for, when called from the MCP or CLI ticket-creation path, records the ticket's channel rather than the python default."],"finding":"When ensure_identity_for is triggered as a side-effect of an MCP or CLI create_ticket call, it will record creation_channel=python (its default) rather than the caller's channel (mcp or cli), because the plan threads the channel explicitly only to the direct identity creation path (create_identity_core/identity_cli) but not to the ensure_identity_for side-effect path invoked during ticket creation. No AC explicitly tests this cross-path scenario, so the MCP and CLI facade tests can go green while the identity CREATE event records the wrong channel for auditors.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fc31dd0b21381a526","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"AC2 (MCP creates identity), AC1 (CLI), Files: src/rebar/_commands/identity.py / composer.py","norm_id":"n6b8f91f44ed88837","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["An auditor queries identity creation events and finds channel=python for identities first created via MCP or CLI ticket creation, contradicting the ticket's own channel record.","The MCP facade test passes (it directly calls create_identity with mcp) while the side-effect identity CREATE from create_ticket is silently wrong."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Either propagate the calling channel from create_core into its ensure_identity_for invocation (passing it through), or add a note in Scope/AC that the ensure_identity_for side-effect channel is intentionally python until e622 and exclude it from AC2/AC1 to avoid false confidence.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"na","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Confirm whether `validate_creation_channel` in `_version.py` needs to be an extracted function (for the contract test) or whether importing the vocabulary constant (`CREATION_CHANNELS` frozenset) directly in the test achieves the same drift-prevention guarantee with less indirection, given it has exactly one production call site today.","cohort":["A1"],"criteria":["A1"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["grep for `validate_creation_channel` returns zero hits in the codebase — no existing call sites","grep for `create_core(` returns 6 call sites total; the validator would be invoked from exactly one of them","Priority validation (lines 119-120 of composer.py) and ticket_type validation (lines 106-111) are inline — the established pattern for single-site validation","Plan rationale: 'add the matching runtime constant plus validate_creation_channel(...) helper to src/rebar/reducer/_version.py and a contract test that prevents runtime/schema vocabulary drift'","`validate_tag_name` — the closest analog — has 3 call sites (leaf.py ×2, composer.py ×1), satisfying Rule-of-Three"],"finding":"The proposed `validate_creation_channel(...)` helper in `reducer/_version.py` has exactly one production call site (`create_core` in `composer.py`), making it a Rule-of-Three borderline abstraction. The plan's secondary rationale — 'a contract test that prevents runtime/schema vocabulary drift' — is legitimate but equally achievable by importing the vocabulary constant directly into the test, as is already done for `KNOWN_EVENT_TYPES`. Existing single-site validation in `create_core` (priority, ticket_type) is inline, not extracted.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f7a2323ec2a1427ee","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What / Files sections: `reducer/_version.py` — `validate_creation_channel` helper","norm_id":"n161cfc33ae33de91","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["The contract-test goal is achievable by importing the CREATION_CHANNELS frozenset constant directly in the test — no extracted function required at 1 call site.","If additional callers (Jira inbound, import) are added in e622, the Rule-of-Three would be satisfied retroactively; the plan could note this explicitly."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"If the primary motivation is the drift test, expose a module-level constant `CREATION_CHANNELS: frozenset[str] = frozenset({\"cli\", \"mcp\", \"python\", \"jira\", \"import\", \"unknown\"})` in `_version.py` and perform inline validation in `create_core` (mirroring the priority/ticket_type pattern). The contract test can then assert `CREATION_CHANNELS == set(schema_enum)` directly without an extracted helper.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.1429,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"na","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Evaluate whether the `gen_types.py` `{\"const\": true}` → `Literal[True]` extension is justified for a single field (`creation_channel_inferred`), or whether typing it as `NotRequired[bool]` in the TypedDict (without generator change) adequately serves consumers until a second `const`-typed field arrives in the generated surface.","cohort":["A1"],"criteria":["A1"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["grep for `\"const\"` in schema files shows only `workflow.v1/v2/v3.schema.json` using const, and none of those are in `TOP_LEVEL_OBJECTS` in gen_types.py","`_pytype` in gen_types.py (lines 115-149) has no `const` branch today — the extension is additive but single-use","Plan quote: 'Encode the marker as {\"const\": true}; recorded and unknown projections omit it' — meaning `creation_channel_inferred` is `True` only when the inferred flag is set, absent otherwise","Plan quote: 'Extend src/rebar/schemas/gen_types.py so JSON Schema {\"const\": true} generates Literal[True]'"],"finding":"The plan extends `gen_types.py` to handle `{\"const\": true}` → `Literal[True]` for the `creation_channel_inferred` field. After this story, exactly one schema property in the generated surface will use `const`, making this a single-use generator extension. The existing workflow schemas use `\"const\": \"1\"/\"2\"/\"3\"` but are not in `TOP_LEVEL_OBJECTS`, so the generator never processes them today. The plan does not evaluate whether the `creation_channel_inferred` marker needs to appear in the TypedDict at all, given the plan itself states 'recorded and unknown projections omit it' (i.e. it is always absent at runtime for the vast majority of tickets).","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f00523d0a03157763","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What / Files sections: `schemas/gen_types.py` — `{\"const\": true}` → `Literal[True]` extension; `ticket_state.schema.json` — `creation_channel_inferred` field","norm_id":"nf3ea3b1d94191b77","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["If `creation_channel_inferred` is modeled as `NotRequired[Literal[True]]` in the TypedDict, type-checkers will correctly flag any code that assigns `False` to it — but the practical value is low for a field that is almost always absent.","Alternatively, `creation_channel_inferred` could be typed as `NotRequired[bool]` in the TypedDict without any generator change, at the cost of slightly weaker typing. The generator extension would then be deferred until a second const field arrives."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.1429,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"na","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add `src/rebar/_io/import_ndjson.py` (and optionally `src/rebar/_io/_provenance.py`) to the Files section with a note that they temporarily acquire `creation_channel=python` as a deliberate delivery-boundary choice, to be overridden by e622.","cohort":["G1G2"],"criteria":["G1G2"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["src/rebar/_io/import_ndjson.py line 167-175: `from rebar import ... create_ticket ...`","src/rebar/_io/import_ndjson.py line 229: `local = create_ticket(repo_root=rr, **_provenance.create_kwargs(rec))`","Plan's Files section lists composer.py, _lib_writes.py, _mcp_writes.py, idea.py, session_log.py, identity.py, reducer/_version.py, reducer/_processors.py, schemas, types.py, and tests — but not _io/import_ndjson.py or _io/_provenance.py."],"finding":"`src/rebar/_io/import_ndjson.py` is a direct caller of `rebar.create_ticket` (line 229) and will be affected by the creation_channel threading — temporarily attributing all NDJSON-imported tickets as `python` until e622 — but it is absent from the plan's Files section.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fff6b1d116f8d435d","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Files section (does not enumerate _io/import_ndjson.py); What section: 'this temporarily gives NDJSON import python without breaking the 6fe2 delivery boundary'","norm_id":"ne45f0eca0f3e2832","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["A reviewer of the PR diff might not realize import_ndjson.py's behavior changes (it silently starts attributing imports as 'python') because it is not listed as a changed file.","The AC regression test `tests/interfaces/facades/test_library.py` must remain green, but no AC probe verifies that import_ndjson.py is correctly channeled — the temporary 'python' attribution is an intentional behavior change that goes undocumented in the Files section."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.4286,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"na","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify the complete `const`-handling rule in gen_types: (a) the insertion point in _pytype() (before or after the `enum` check), (b) the fallback for `const` values other than `True` (e.g., emit `Literal[<value>]` generically, or restrict to booleans only and map others to their scalar type), and (c) precedence when `const` and `type` both appear.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan: 'Extend src/rebar/schemas/gen_types.py so JSON Schema {\"const\": true} generates Literal[True]'","Plan: 'Encode the marker as {\"const\": true}; recorded and unknown projections omit it'","Current gen_types._pytype() handles: $ref, enum, list-type, array, object, null-type — no `const` branch exists","No fallback for non-boolean const values is stated anywhere in the plan","The plan delivers only the single example case `const: true → Literal[True]`; all other const values are unspecified"],"finding":"The plan requires extending gen_types._pytype() to handle JSON Schema `{\"const\": true}` and emit `Literal[True]`, but never specifies: (a) where in the _pytype() dispatch chain the `const` branch is inserted, (b) what gen_types does for any other `const` value (e.g., `const: 1`, `const: \"string\"`), or (c) how `const` interacts with a co-present `type` key. The current _pytype() has no `const` branch at all. An implementer is left to invent the fallback and the sequencing rule.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fe47d99b3829cd248","impact":0.33,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section ('Extend src/rebar/schemas/gen_types.py so JSON Schema {\"const\": true} generates Literal[True]') and AC #6 ('gen_types renders const true as Literal[True]') vs. src/rebar/schemas/gen_types.py _pytype() lines 115–149","norm_id":"n57da065246a4b121","priority":0.1237,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["An implementer adds a `const` branch that only handles `True`; a future schema that uses `const: 1` or `const: 'fixed'` silently falls through to `Any` or raises KeyError","A `const` node that also carries `type: boolean` is handled by the type branch instead of the const branch, yielding `bool` instead of `Literal[True]`"],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add a sentence to the What section: 'In _pytype(), check for `\"const\" in node` BEFORE the `type` dispatch and emit `Literal[<repr(node[\"const\"])>]` for any const value (not just True); this covers both the boolean inference marker and any future single-value const fields.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"na","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Clarify the immutability protocol for non-EDIT event processors: either confirm that STATUS/LINK/JIRA_BIND never touch creation_channel by construction (and state why), or name the guard/check that enforces it and include those processors in the AC test scope.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan: 'process_edit skips those names before its generic assignment, while specialized processors never assign them' — no processing rule for specialized processors stated","LINK, STATUS, JIRA_BIND processors are not in the Files list and no change is specified for them","The immutability claim for non-EDIT events is asserted ('never assign them') but no mechanism or test location is given for those paths"],"finding":"The plan asserts that 'STATUS, LINK, JIRA_BIND, plus other specialized events also cannot replace genesis provenance' but provides no processing protocol for those event types — only EDIT gets an explicit mechanism (_IMMUTABLE_EDIT_FIELDS guard in process_edit). For STATUS, LINK, and JIRA_BIND there is no co-located decision rule, no named guard, and no file/function location specified. The claim is structural but the rule is missing.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fd4bcf9509a590aeb","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section: '_IMMUTABLE_EDIT_FIELDS = frozenset({\"creation_channel\", \"creation_channel_inferred\"}) in reducer/_processors.py; process_edit skips those names… STATUS, LINK, JIRA_BIND, plus other specialized events also cannot replace genesis provenance'","norm_id":"nee0dc51098242163","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["A future EDIT processor change inadvertently adds creation_channel assignment before the immutable-field guard fires — not caught because the guard sequencing within process_edit is unspecified","A reviewer implementing AC #5 ('STATUS, LINK, JIRA_BIND, plus other specialized events also cannot replace genesis provenance') has no spec to test against for non-EDIT events"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"na","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Pin the legacy-fallback projection rule to its host location in the plan (e.g., 'in process_create, when CREATE.data carries no creation_channel key, set state[\"creation_channel\"] = \"unknown\" and omit creation_channel_inferred') and add reducer/_processors.py to the Files list for this change.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan What: 'A legacy CREATE with no value provisionally projects creation_channel=unknown without creation_channel_inferred. Child e622 treats absent/None/unknown-without-marker as unresolved legacy input'","Files list names reducer/_processors.py only for '_IMMUTABLE_EDIT_FIELDS', not for the legacy fallback projection","process_create in _processors.py is the only place where CREATE.data is read and mapped to compiled state, but it is not named for this change"],"finding":"The legacy-fallback projection rule ('A legacy CREATE with no value provisionally projects creation_channel=unknown without creation_channel_inferred') is stated in the What section and in AC #4, but is never pinned to a specific processor or location in the reducer. process_create in reducer/_processors.py is the natural home, but the plan's Files list does not include _processors.py for this rule, and the What section only says 'Store creation_channel in CREATE.data for every new local creation and project it into compiled state exactly once' — which describes new writes, not the legacy-fallback projection.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fb792c03cfcccf979","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section: 'A legacy CREATE with no value provisionally projects creation_channel=unknown without creation_channel_inferred' vs. Files list (reducer/_processors.py not named for this rule)","norm_id":"n63f9338314534727","priority":0.099,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["An implementer adds the legacy fallback in _version.py (near the runtime constant) instead of process_create, causing the projection to fire at validation time rather than at reduce time","The 'exactly once' constraint is violated if both the write path and process_create emit a default"],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add to the Files list entry for reducer/_processors.py: 'process_create: when CREATE.data has no creation_channel, set state[\"creation_channel\"] = \"unknown\" (no creation_channel_inferred key) as the legacy provisional fallback.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify in the implementation note that `_IMMUTABLE_EDIT_FIELDS` must be checked INSIDE the loop body, AFTER the `field_name not in state` guard (i.e., as the first check in the 'key is present' branch), and add an AC sub-note confirming the test creates a ticket (so creation_channel is in state) THEN attempts the EDIT — not the reverse.","cohort":["G6"],"criteria":["G6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":"novelty","evidence":["Current process_edit (lines 485-510 of reducer/_processors.py): the ONLY guard before assignment is `if field_name not in state: continue`. Once `creation_channel` is in state (added by process_create), this guard no longer protects it.","Plan says 'process_edit skips those names before its generic assignment' — 'generic assignment' is `state[field_name] = new_value`; the frozenset check must be inserted between the key-presence check and that assignment line.","No existing immutable-field guard pattern exists in the codebase to serve as a reference implementation; this is novel guard logic."],"finding":"The plan specifies that `process_edit` must skip `creation_channel` and `creation_channel_inferred` via `_IMMUTABLE_EDIT_FIELDS`, but does not specify WHERE in the existing `process_edit` control flow the guard is inserted. The current code's first guard is `if field_name not in state: continue`, which will pass through once `creation_channel` is seeded into state by `process_create`. If an implementer inserts the frozenset check AFTER the existing key-presence guard (i.e., only inside the branch where the key IS in state), the immutability protection works correctly. But the plan's description only says 'process_edit skips those names before its generic assignment' — 'before' is relative to 'generic assignment', which could be read as before the `state[field_name] = new_value` line specifically (correct) OR before the entire field loop (over-broad). This ambiguity creates a real risk that an implementer guards the wrong branch or placement, leaving `creation_channel` mutable via EDIT on tickets where it was already projected.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f35a1802a4199ff0e","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section: 'Define _IMMUTABLE_EDIT_FIELDS = frozenset({\"creation_channel\", \"creation_channel_inferred\"}) in reducer/_processors.py; process_edit skips those names before its generic assignment'","norm_id":"nf30ff9a5e81f9c0a","priority":0.132,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An EDIT event carrying creation_channel='mcp' on a CLI-created ticket would overwrite the genesis provenance if the guard is inserted at the wrong level (e.g., added as an elif branch in _parse_tag_list instead of in the core loop).","A future refactor of process_edit that collapses the key-presence check could silently drop the protection."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add to the What section: 'In `process_edit`, insert `if field_name in _IMMUTABLE_EDIT_FIELDS: continue` as the FIRST statement inside the `else` branch after `if field_name not in state: continue` — i.e., after the key-presence guard but before `state[field_name] = new_value`.' The AC test for the immutable criterion must create a ticket first (so `creation_channel` is in state), then send an EDIT containing `creation_channel`, and assert the value is unchanged.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.5,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a `process_snapshot` migration guard (analogous to the `managed_refs`/`attestations`/`keyring` guards) that sets `creation_channel = 'unknown'` when `creation_channel` is absent from the restored `compiled_state`, and confirm the AC `legacy` test exercises a ticket replayed through a SNAPSHOT (not only a bare CREATE event).","cohort":["T11"],"criteria":["T11"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":"novelty","evidence":["Plan: 'A legacy CREATE with no value provisionally projects creation_channel=unknown without creation_channel_inferred.'","Plan: 'Store creation_channel in CREATE.data for every new local creation and project it into compiled state exactly once.'","Plan is SILENT on process_snapshot migration for legacy compiled_state lacking creation_channel.","process_snapshot verbatim bulk-copy: `for key, value in compiled_state.items(): state[key] = value` — absent keys stay absent.","Precedent guards already exist for managed_refs (seeded), attestations (folded), and keyring (re-seeded) in process_snapshot."],"finding":"The plan specifies `creation_channel=unknown` as the fallback for a legacy CREATE lacking the field, but does not address how `process_snapshot` handles a SNAPSHOT (compiled_state) written before this feature. Existing code restores compiled_state verbatim; without an explicit migration guard (like those for `managed_refs`, `attestations`, and `keyring`), tickets compacted before the feature ships will emerge from the SNAPSHOT path with `creation_channel` absent — not `unknown` — silently defeating the legacy-ticket fallback contract.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f10693fb223d27c27","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What / reducer projection section; reducer/_processors.py process_snapshot; compared with `managed_refs`, `attestations`, `keyring` guards in the same function","norm_id":"n9adbc3446cf9be37","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A ticket compacted (SNAPSHOTted) before this story ships is shown/listed after deployment: the SNAPSHOT path restores compiled_state without creation_channel, so the field is absent in output despite the 'unknown fallback' promise.","The AC test for `legacy` tickets passes against a freshly-created legacy-style CREATE event but fails against a real compacted legacy ticket, giving false green on CI."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"In `process_snapshot`, after the bulk restore, add: `if 'creation_channel' not in compiled_state: state['creation_channel'] = 'unknown'`. Do NOT set `creation_channel_inferred` here (the marker must be absent for legacy/unknown, matching the plan's intent that e622 can positively infer). Update the `legacy` AC test to include a compacted fixture.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.75,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"medium","reversibility":"moderate","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}}],"impact_model_version":"plan-v3","material_fingerprint":"c5eeb606d9857295","metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":221.7,"llm_calls":30,"llm_ms":679510.3,"total_ms":679844.1,"verify_requests":31},"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","regver":"b293b9a55de591cc","runner":"pydantic_ai","schema":"plan_review_result_v2","ticket_id":"6fe2-ab22-c231-4a41","ticket_type":"story","verdict":"BLOCK","verified_at_sha":"faa40e7b07b1ebfd7f0a12e122e9017b0cdd0b35"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"REVIEW_RESULT","timestamp":1784268783352877001,"uuid":"7ce68e70-f2bd-471e-b271-6b95b007a26d"}